{"id":24172,"title":"Hepatectomy for liver abscess caused by stones spilled during laparoscopic cholecystectomy.","abstract":"An abdominal abscess caused by spilled stones is a serious complication of laparoscopic cholecystectomy that requires drainage or reoperation to remove the scattered stones. Herein, we report the case of a 50-year-old woman, who was on dialysis for renal failure. She underwent major hepatectomy for a liver abscess caused by stones spilled during laparoscopic cholecystectomy. ","date":"2014-01-23","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24450346","annotations":[{"name":"Dialysis","weight":0.760896,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dialysis"},{"name":"Abdomen","weight":0.752214,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abdomen"},{"name":"Liver","weight":0.740492,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liver"},{"name":"Abscess","weight":0.730934,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abscess"},{"name":"Renal failure","weight":0.729617,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Renal_failure"},{"name":"Laparoscopic surgery","weight":0.702154,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laparoscopic_surgery"},{"name":"Kidney","weight":0.678276,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kidney"},{"name":"Cholecystectomy","weight":0.285578,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cholecystectomy"},{"name":"Kidney stone","weight":0.204746,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kidney_stone"},{"name":"Hepatectomy","weight":0.161238,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hepatectomy"},{"name":"Complication (medicine)","weight":0.101782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complication_(medicine)"},{"name":"Drainage","weight":0.0300804,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drainage"},{"name":"Liver abscess","weight":0.0274275,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/